snippet.textDisplay:
Ok but is no one going to talk about how he's multiplying the dimensions with the density in the WRONG UNITS?!
He calculated the dimensions of the 1st block in centimetres and multiplied with the density in kg/m3. Then AGAIN calculated dimensions of the largest block in metres and multiplied with the density in gm/cm3.
So the mass of the 1st block came out WAY MORE than expected and the mass of the largest block came out LESS than expected.
Then again I haven't personally done the calculations so I'm not sure if he converted them before calculating but the editor messed up, man.
